body.plain: You is a single by Greta Isaac which explores the obsession and infatuation with another person to extremities.

annotations:
What I would do to get into your head
 Crawl out my body into yours instead

This shows that the character wants to become the other person, that they want the same thought process and the same body: that they want to embody them.
In an interview with Clash Magazine, Greta Isaac said

The character is infatuated with another person to such an extreme that she abandons her own identity to embody the other person."

This is the theme within the song.
Over and over and over and over again
This line intertwines into the theme of obsession by using repetition. It shows that Isaac is obsessed with this person by saying she does everything in the first verse “over and over again”.

description.plain: “We wanted something that sounded like anxiety, a quick heartbeat, that urgency. This rising panic. We just bashed it out in an hour. It sounded like a dance track that we were thinking of pitching to someone. But when we put the guitar in it became so gnarly. It’s probably the most on the nose in terms of just wanting to be validated and how that is my intention behind everything I do. But I still wanted it to sound like a euphoric release, for it to give you relief from any panic that I felt. I never get bored of it, I love it!” – Greta Isaac via https://riotmag.co/listen-to-greta-isaacs-huge-new-single-like-me

description.plain:
WELCOME TO GENIUS' MARCH 2022 SINGLES RELEASE CALENDAR!!!



For March 2022 album releases, visit this page



This page highlights the notable singles released in all genres throughout March 2022. Each song title includes a hyperlink to the corresponding lyric page.

HOW CAN YOU HELP?


Adding songs



If there’s a notable song you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you notice that any of the songs on this list haven’t been transcribed, go to the corresponding page and add in lyrics!


Updating dates



If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.

If there’s a notable song you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you notice that any of the songs on this list haven’t been transcribed, go to the corresponding page and add in lyrics!


Updating dates



If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.
